muros (0.9.47) trixie; urgency=medium

  * High availability: port the CARP/pfsync data plane to native Debian tooling.
    CARP virtual IPs (virtualip/vip mode=carp) are now realised as keepalived
    VRRP instances and the pfsync state channel as conntrackd. A new generator
    (vrrp.inc) renders /etc/keepalived/keepalived.conf and
    /etc/conntrackd/conntrackd.conf from config.xml and starts the services only
    when CARP VIPs and an HA sync interface are configured. The advskew is
    mapped to the VRRP priority, addresses sharing an interface and vhid are
    grouped into one instance, and a notify hook records the master/backup role
    and drives the conntrackd failover. The CARP status, maintenance and
    enable/disable controls and the monit CARP check now read this state instead
    of the FreeBSD net.inet.carp.* sysctls. keepalived and conntrackd move to
    Recommends and are disabled at boot (MurOS starts them on demand).

