muros (0.9.39) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Loopback: stop adding a redundant 127.0.0.1/32 to the loopback interface.
    The Linux kernel already configures lo with 127.0.0.1/8 and ::1/128, so the
    FreeBSD-era "ifconfig lo0 inet 127.0.0.1" (which iproute2 stores as a /32
    host address) only produced a duplicate alongside the kernel address. The
    loopback is now left to the kernel; only loopback VIPs and the up state are
    still applied.
  * Credentials: keep a single administrative password across the web UI and the
    console/SSH. A new optional PAM hook (muros-passwd-sync, wired into
    common-password through pam-auth-update) mirrors a password set with passwd
    into the web UI configuration as a bcrypt hash, complementing the existing
    config.xml to /etc/shadow synchronisation. Changing the password on the
    console and in the web UI now keeps both in sync.

