muros (0.9.34) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Firewall dashboard widget / log viewer: populate them with default block
    traffic. The input and forward chains relied on the nftables "policy drop"
    to discard unmatched packets, which never logs, so the firewall log was
    permanently empty. nft_build.php now appends an explicit logged drop ("log
    prefix muros,block,default") at the end of both chains, honouring the
    syslog/nologdefaultblock option exactly like the legacy filter did. Blocked
    traffic now shows up in the firewall log viewer and the dashboard widget.

  * Dashboard memory and disk gauges: enlarge them. The half doughnut capped its
    radius at half the cell width, leaving the lower half of the widget empty and
    the readout cramped. BaseGaugeWidget now draws a 270 degree gauge that uses
    the cell height too, with the value and detail text centred in the ring, so
    the gauges read clearly without changing the widget footprint.

 -- MurOS <dev@muros.org>  Sun, 21 Jun 2026 09:05:00 +0000

muros (0.9.33) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Dashboard live widgets: fix the CPU, network traffic and firewall log graphs
    staying empty. These widgets consume server-sent event streams that the MVC
    layer writes line by line as configd produces them. The stock Debian php.ini
    ships output_buffering = 4096 and implicit_flush = Off, so php-fpm held the
    small per-second chunks in its output buffer and the browser never received
    a single event, leaving the graphs blank. debian/stage-fs.sh now appends
    output_buffering = Off and implicit_flush = On to the web SAPI 99-muros.ini
    so streamed responses are flushed on every write.

