muros (0.9.16) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Runtime directories: create /var/etc (and the PHP temp/session/cache tree)
    at boot through a systemd-tmpfiles drop-in installed at the path systemd
    actually scans (/usr/lib/tmpfiles.d/muros.conf). On FreeBSD this tree came
    from the mtree /var specification applied by the rc boot scripts, which do
    not run on Debian, so generated service configuration could not be written
    (rename() of dnsmasq hosts/leases and similar files failed with "No such
